            {"title": "yield — Calling a Block", "content": "<p>Inside a method, <code>yield</code> calls the block that was passed by the caller. Use <code>block_given?</code> to check if a block was provided before yielding.</p><pre style='background:#1e1e2f;color:#e2e8f0;padding:15px;border-radius:8px;'>def greet\n  puts \"Before block\"\n  yield \"Ruby\" if block_given?\n  puts \"After block\"\nend\n\ngreet { |lang| puts \"Hello from #{lang}!\" }</pre>"},
