            {"title": "Mixins with include", "content": "<pre style='background:#1e1e2f;color:#e2e8f0;padding:15px;border-radius:8px;'>module Greetable\n  def greet\n    \"Hello, I am #{name}\"\n  end\nend\n\nclass Person\n  include Greetable\n  attr_reader :name\n  def initialize(name); @name = name; end\nend\n\nputs Person.new(\"Alice\").greet  # Hello, I am Alice</pre>"},
            {"title": "Comparable & Enumerable — Built-in Modules", "content": "<p>Ruby's standard library ships powerful modules. Including <code>Comparable</code> and defining <code>&lt;=&gt;</code> gives you <code>&lt;</code>, <code>&gt;</code>, <code>between?</code>, <code>clamp</code>. Including <code>Enumerable</code> and defining <code>each</code> gives you all 50+ collection methods like <code>map</code>, <code>select</code>, <code>sort</code>, <code>min</code>, <code>group_by</code>, etc.</p>"},
