        key_concepts="<ul><li>Always use block form: <code>File.open('f', 'r') { |f| ... }</code> — ensures file is closed.</li><li>File modes: <code>'r'</code> read, <code>'w'</code> write (truncates), <code>'a'</code> append, <code>'r+'</code> read+write.</li><li><code>chomp</code> removes trailing newline from a string.</li><li>For CSV files, use Ruby's built-in <code>csv</code> library: <code>require 'csv'</code>.</li><li>Handle <code>Errno::ENOENT</code> (file not found) and <code>Errno::EACCES</code> (permission denied).</li></ul>",
